			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Has anyone done a study on the effects of equipping a pet with good bazaar bought gear?
<br />

<br />
It would seem that a mage dishing out 1-2k (or more for some of the truly rich) in the bazaar could equip a pet substantially more than with just summoned gear, resulting in a significant boost to not only HP and dex/agi (for more ability procs), but to AC also.  I'd imagine a good enough weapon might be able to increase damage per hit also.
<br />

<br />
Could this lead to increased survivability significantly large enough to merit dishing out a few k in cash?  I would certainly be willing to drop a good few plat if it would increase my AA xp-ing by 50% (and cash flow also), and maybe allow me to take on a few mobs that otherwise wouldn't be worth the effort.
<br />

<br />
Maybe when I'm feeling richer (after I finish buying all my spells), I'll try to do just this.  If no one's tried this yet, any suggestions on affordable gear which would give the most bang for the buck?  I'm thinking maybe some of the LDoN stuff that drops constantly, so is pretty cheap in the bazaar, but I don't know specifics.
<br />

<br />
-Dretchulos
<br />
-65th season mage of Torvonnilous</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
