				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am an expert at giving pets weapons, having also tested it all recently levelling a necromancer, and tested previously with shadow knight skeletons and lower level elementals.  Here are the facts:
<br />

<br />
1) Pets, like all NPCs, destroy any <span style="font-style: italic">NO DROP</span> item given to them.  This is to prevent an earlier exploit of using the corpse of a dead mob to transfer <span style="font-style: italic">NO DROP</span> gear via looting.
<br />

<br />
2) Skeletons and elementals summoned by spells up to level 34 will wield two handed weapons usefully.  Starting level 44, they will not wield two handers.
<br />

<br />
3) Starting with the very first spell circle, skeletons and elementals will deal a maximum of twice the stated damage of the weapon, or their normal damage, whichever is higher.  Thus, an <span style="font-style: italic">Elementalkin</span> given a <span style="font-style: italic">Weighty Polearm</span> will hit for 58.
<br />

<br />
4) So far as I can tell, <span style="font-style: italic">A Weighted Axe</span> is the only weapon specifically hard-coded against pets.  All other 2-handers are pet-wieldable, regardless of class or race, including <span style="font-style: italic">Tantor's Tusk</span>, which allows the pet to hit for 100.
<br />

<br />
5) Pets ignore recommended levels for damage, as well as stats.
<br />

<br />
6) Pets benefit from stats on weapons and armor, especially AC, hit points, strength, and dexterity.
<br />

<br />
7) Pets do not benefit from focus effects on an item they are wielding.
<br />

<br />
8) Pets prock with weapons at the same level as players.
<br />

<br />
9) A pet which is alive solely due to hitpoints from gear will act oddly, not moving or obeying orders, until it regenerates sufficient hitpoints to stand on its own.
<br />

<br />
10) It is possible to get a level 34 pet to dual wield using a two-hander in its primary and a one hander in its off hand.  Both weapons strike with the appropriate damage, procks, and hit verbs.  However, I have not discerned the pattern of what weapons it will and will not dual wield, so proceed with caution.
<br />

<br />
These are the facts, which I have personally confirmed recently multiple times.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Razamatazz Pizzazz</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
